; remarks: the medial surstylus was displaced anteriorly, and it is visible only in anterior view. This displacement frequently happens when the male terminalia are dissected, which makes the examination of the medial surstylus and the general shape of the terminalia difficult). Prensiseta developed and slightly curved, with acuminate apex (
