Type material. Lectotype male, by present designation, MCZ
(
Figs. 19‒28
): “ 288 ” [small grey label], “Loew\coll.”, “ appendiculata \m.” [handwritten], “ Type \ 13280 ” [red label] (
Fig. 20
); “ Lectotype ” [red] label was added. The lectotype is relatively well preserved ( Figs. 19, 20 ), except for the dirt on body; the abdomen was detached beyond tergite 3 , cleared and placed in glycerine in a micro-vial attached to the pin of the specimen.
